The paper discusses logic encryption techniques to prevent security threats, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a modeling framework and metrics to evaluate the security level and trade-offs, which involves logic and optimization (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper addresses the challenges of conflicting security concerns, which can be related to cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of compound encryption methods, which can be related to programming languages (cs.PL).
